omWeb?topicID=32.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Detect Hidden FAQ</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  1) When do I get detect hidden?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
You get detect hidden ability when you attain a natural 16 spec in stealth.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  2) Who gets detect hidden?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The detect hidden ability is given only to assassin classes (nightshade, shadowblade, infiltrator).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  3) How does detect hidden work?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Long answer, so first a few definitions:<br>
<br>
Hider - The person that is stealthed<br>
<br>
Seeker - The person seeking the stealthed person<br>
<br>
/loc unit - Distance measured in the units that /loc gives you.  /loc prints the location as 4 numbers.  The x location, the y location, the z location and the directional facing, based on 360 degree compass reading. 0 = north.  Distance between two points: sqrt( (x1 - x2)^2 + (y1 - y2)^2 )   One human-sized horse is approximately 125 /loc units long.<br>
<br>
Characters with the detect hidden ability are able to detect a hider within a minimum detect radius that depends on the class of the hider.<br>
<br>
When seeking an archer class, the minimum radius of detection is 250 /loc units.  When seeking other assassins, the minimum radius of detection is 125 /loc units.  For each character level of the seeker higher than the spec level of stealth of the hider, add 50 /loc units to this radius.  <br>
<br>
For characters without the detect hidden ability, the minimum distance for seeing all hiders is 125 /loc units, adding 20 units to the radius for each character level of the seeker above the spec level of stealth of the hider.<br>
<br>
In both cases, if the stealth level of the hider is higher than the character level of the seeker, the appropriate minimum detect radius is used.  For purposes of hider stealth spec, items and realm rank bonuses are included.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 4) So, does stealth over 50 help me?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
With the way detect hidden works, no.  Your targets in RvR are a max level of 50.  And since it compares your stealth to their level, anything over 50 means that their detect radius will be the minimum distance (125 /loc units).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 5) Does the z-axis have anything to do with the calculations?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I have to say that for the time being, I don't know.  All my testing was done on flat ground.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 6) Why don't I see stealthers sometimes even though I know they are within my detect radius?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The client receives stealthed char info about once every 3 seconds.  So depending on where you are and where they are when that 3 second 'tick' happens, it's possible to walk right by someone without being seen if you get lucky.  Never assume you're safe though, would be my advice. <p>-- Huff McTuff, 41 Nightshade, Pendragon<br>
