And your question about 51 stealth .. should read 50 stealth, then the answer would be &quot;yes&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uditherdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dither DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 5:19:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/dither/smiley2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden FAQ</span><hr size=1> in order for the casters to get line of sight,t hey cant pan out like we do when we check climb points.  also, many people simply dont know where climb points are, nor the finer details of stealth and detection.  Personally, I leave the info unknown, unless someone i am grouped with asks me how it works.  If they don't want to group, but want free anti rogue info, screw 'em imo 8) <p><a href="http://daoc.catacombs.com/cbuilder.cfm?template=38056&raceid=10&classid=44">Dither Disgustipated</a><BR>
