<a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/bbhamers">Ragnarok</a>, <a href="http://www.palomides.net">Palomides</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utreadlightly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treadlightly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 10:32:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden FAQ</span><hr size=1>     Squink I'm a little confused and would appreciate it if you (or anyone else in the know) can clarify something for me:<br>
<br>
     You said, &quot;When seeking an archer class, the MINIMUM radius of detection is 250 loc units. When seeking other assassins, the MINIMUM radius of detection is 125 loc units... For characters without the detect hidden ability, the MINIMUM distance for seeing all hiders is 125 loc units...&quot;<br>
<br>
     Reading this literally I take this to mean that an Infiltrator (whose character level equals the stealth level of the hider) with the detect hidden ability could see a stealthed archer 250 or more loc units away, but could not detect him if he moved closer to say 200 loc units and that other assassins like Nightshades or Shadowblades (who should have even better stealthing abilities) fare worse because the infiltrator can see them at 125 loc units or more away and that they would need to move within 125 loc units of the Infiltrator to be truly invisible.  Additionally, a pally or cleric of equal level without detect hidden would have the advantage of being able to see both archers and assassins 125 loc units away whereas the Infiltrator could see the assassin but not the archer at that distance.  This is counterintuitive because I would think that the farther away the hider moves from the seeker the harder it is for the seeker to see him.  Therefore I am hoping you meant &quot;maximum radius&quot; not &quot;minimum radius.&quot;   Please help me out here.  <br>
